OL,3,CCouncillor sexually assaulted girl,
OL,4,C13, while she sat on his lap
OL,6,F"As soon as the verdict was known, I
OL,7,Fexpelled Mr Ockelton from the group,
OL,8,Fand I again urged him to resign from
OL,9,Fthe authority, which he has now done."
OL,11,FCouncil chief executive Alistair
OL,12,FCunningham said what the council had
OL,13,Fdiscovered was appalling.
OL,15,F"Whilst we were aware he was on trial,
OL,16,Flegally, as a council, we do not have
OL,17,Fthe power to remove a councillor
OL,18,Funless proven guilty and sentenced,"
OL,19,Fhe said.
